[[Partially valid. Under the new rule, 'a◇b=(a①b)★(a②b)', a◇b would equal (4★2)★(4+2×2)=96, which is different from 11/2. But, in the case of (16★X)◇3, we have (16★X)★(16+2×3)=250, which is the same as the original rule after the change X=11. Hence, even though the first equation doesn't hold, the second one does with X=11. The changes made to the original rule to achieve the same results would be a①b=a^2-b and a②b=a+2b, which are exactly the new rules given.]]
